  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Rich Content</h2>
    <p>List items can contain any flow content, not just text.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/li-rich-content.html" url="li-rich-content.html" title="Rich content in list items" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Multiple elements in list items">{{ richContentCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Nesting Lists</h2>
    <p>List items can contain nested lists to create hierarchical structures. The nested list must be <strong>inside</strong> the <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/li-nesting.html" url="li-nesting.html" title="Nested and mixed lists" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Nested lists">{{ nestedListCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Mixed list types">{{ mixedListCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Value Attribute (Ordered Lists)</h2>
    <p>In ordered lists, use the <code>value</code> attribute to override the item's number. Subsequent items continue from that value.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/li-value.html" url="li-value.html" title="Value attribute" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Value attribute on list items">{{ valueAttributeCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p><strong>Note:</strong> The <code>value</code> attribute only applies to <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> elements within <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code>. It has no effect in <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Screen Reader Behavior</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Announced as "list item" with position (e.g., "bullet, list item 2 of 5")</li>
      <li>In ordered lists, the number is announced</li>
      <li>Nested list items announce their depth level</li>
      <li>Users can navigate between items with keyboard shortcuts</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Always place <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> inside a proper list container</li>
      <li>Keep list items focused on single concepts</li>
      <li>Use meaningful content &mdash; avoid empty list items</li>
      <li>Limit nesting depth to 3 levels for usability</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Common Mistakes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Wrong:</strong> Using <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> outside a list container</li>
      <li><strong>Wrong:</strong> Placing block elements directly between <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;li&gt;</code></li>
      <li><strong>Wrong:</strong> Empty list items for spacing</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

